30/10/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A grenade attack Friday (28 October) in Southern Serbia was linked to the situation in Kosovo, according to Serbia-Montenegro Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic, who is also head of Belgrade's co-ordination body in Southern Serbia.
No injuries were reported in the attack, in which an unknown assailant threw a hand grenade at a police station in the Bunajovac region, causing what authorities termed "significant material damage".
(Tanjug, RTS - 29/10/05)
